&quot;gr:tiktok_pixel:enabled&quot;,&quot;content&quot;:&quot;true&quot;},{&quot;tagName&quot;:&quot;meta&quot;,&quot;headKey&quot;:&quot;meta-property-gr-logged_in_user-id&quot;,&quot;property&quot;:&quot;gr:logged_in_user:id&quot;},{&quot;tagName&quot;:&quot;meta&quot;,&quot;headKey&quot;:&quot;meta-property-gr-page-type&quot;,&quot;property&quot;:&quot;gr:page:type&quot;,&quot;value&quot;:&quot;product&quot;},{&quot;tagName&quot;:&quot;meta&quot;,&quot;headKey&quot;:&quot;meta-name-description&quot;,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;description&quot;,&quot;content&quot;:&quot;Setting up Claude Code yourself is a time sink. You stare at a blank config wondering which subagents to build, what belongs in CLAUDE.md, how to wire up MCP, and how to stop an autonomous agent from running something destructive. Hours gone before you write a line of real code.Claude Code Agent OS is that setup, already done right. Drop it into any repo and Claude Code instantly works like a senior team: it plans, builds, reviews, tests, and ships using specialists you invoke with a single slash command. Go from blank to a pro-grade AI coding workflow in about 5 minutes.WHAT&#39;S INSIDE:- 26 specialized subagents - code-reviewer, security-auditor, test-writer, debugger, refactor-architect, perf-optimizer, api-designer, auth-implementer, db-schema-architect, nextjs-architect, react-component-builder, sql-optimizer, docker-builder, ci-cd-engineer, release-manager, and more- 12 slash commands - /plan, /scaffold, /review, /test, /debug, /refactor, /optimize, /audit-security, /document, /commit, /pr, /ship- 5 ready-to-use CLAUDE.md templates - Next.js, Python, Node API, monorepo, React Native (with real build/test commands and always/never rules)- MCP configs - Filesystem, Memory, Sequential-Thinking, Playwright browser (.mcp.json examples + setup guide; all on maintained servers, verified 2026-06)- Safety + format hooks (bash + Windows PowerShell) - auto-format on save, block dangerous commands (rm -rf / Remove-Item -Recurse -Force), pre-commit lint- 4 workflow playbooks - feature-to-PR, safe refactor, bug fix, releaseWHY YOU&#39;LL LOVE IT:- Stack-agnostic - works with any language or framework, in any repo- Built on real best practices, not generic prompts - each agent has a focused workflow and output format- Plain Markdown/JSON you can read and edit to fit your project- A START HERE QUICKSTART gets you running in 5 minutes; FAQ and per-folder READMEs cover the rest- Instant download - nothing shipsStop configuring and start shipping. Drop in the agents and commands, run /review, and feel the difference on your very next commit.(Single-user commercial license - use it on all your own projects. Please do not resell or redistribute.)&quot;},{&quot;tagName&quot;:&quot;meta&quot;,&quot;headKey&quot;:&quot;meta-property-product-retailer_item_id&quot;,&quot;property&quot;:&quot;product:retailer_item_id&quot;,&quot;content&quot;:&quot;womhu&quot;},{&quot;tagName&quot;:&quot;meta&quot;,&quot;headKey&quot;:&quot;meta-property-product-price-amount&quot;,&quot;property&quot;:&quot;product:price:amount&quot;,&quot;content&quot;:29.0},{&quot;tagName&quot;:&quot;meta&quot;,&quot;headKey&quot;:&quot;meta-property-product-price-currency&quot;,&quot;property&quot;:&quot;product:price:currency&quot;,&quot;content&quot;:&quot;USD&quot;},{&quot;tagName&quot;:&quot;meta&quot;,&quot;headKey&quot;:&quot;meta-property-og-description&quot;,&quot;property&quot;:&quot;og:description&quot;,&quot;value&quot;:&quot;Setting up Claude Code yourself is a time sink. You stare at a blank config wondering which subagents to build, what belongs in CLAUDE.md, how to wire up MCP, and how to stop an autonomous agent from running something destructive. Hours gone before you write a line of real code.Claude Code Agent OS is that setup, already done right. Drop it into any repo and Claude Code instantly works like a senior team: it plans, builds, reviews, tests, and ships using specialists you invoke wit